SIMPLE: wrestle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrestle
<hw>Wres"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Wrestled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Wrestling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wrestlen</ets>, <ets>wrastlen</ets>, AS. <ets>wr<?/stlian</ets>,
freq. of <ets>wr<?/stan</ets> to wrest; akin to OD. <ets>wrastelen</ets>
to <ets>wrestle</ets>. See <er>Wrest</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To contend, by grappling with, and striving to trip
or throw down, an opponent; <as>as, they <ex>wrestled</ex>
skillfully</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To-morrow, sir, I <qex>wrestle</qex> for my credit, and he that
escapes me without some broken limb shall acquit him well.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Another, by a fall in <qex>wrestling</qex>, started the end of the
clavicle from the sternum.</q> <rj><qau>Wiseman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to struggle; to strive earnestly; to
contend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Come, <qex>wrestle</qex> with thy affections.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We <qex>wrestle</qex> not against flesh and blood.</q>
<rj><qau>Eph. vi. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Difficulties with which he had himself <qex>wrestled</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrestle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wrestle
<hw>Wres"tle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To wrestle with; to seek to
throw down as in wrestling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrestle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wrestle
<hw>Wres"tle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A struggle between two persons to
see which will throw the other down; a bout at wrestling; a wrestling
match; a struggle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whom in a <qex>wrestle</qex> the giant catching aloft, with a
terrible hug broke three of his ribs.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrestler</ent>⟦br⟧
